===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{zh-etym-double|木|tree}} to give the idea of multiple trees (compare {{zh-l|*森}}), thus a forest. See also the top component of [[散]] in its original version.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*rəm||jungle; forest; country; field}} (STEDT under PTB *ram). Cognate with {{och-l|森|forest}}, {{cog|lus|ram||forest; country}}, {{cog|mjw|ram||jungle}}.

Or perhaps an area word ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), shared with {{cog|km|រាម||thick bushy jungle that grows along a stream}}, {{cog|okz|*rām||inundated forest along a watercourse}}, {{cog|okz|sarāma ~ sarāṃ||a tract of stunted vegetation}}, {{cog|mnw|ရာံ|tr=rèm|t=copse; patch of woodland}}.

